<%# /privacy -- Privacy Policy. v7 layout (light, editorial).
    Rendered via renderV7(reply, 'privacy', data).
    Operating legal entity: OrgTP, LLC. Baseline copy -- counsel to review
    before relying on it. `lastUpdated` is passed in by the route. %>
<style>
  .legal-wrap { max-width: 780px; }
  .legal-prose h2 {
    font-family:'Schibsted Grotesk','Inter',sans-serif; font-weight:700;
    font-size:clamp(1.2rem,2.2vw,1.55rem); letter-spacing:-0.01em;
    color:var(--ink); line-height:1.25; margin-top:2.6rem;
  }
  .legal-prose h2:first-child { margin-top:0; }
  .legal-prose p, .legal-prose li { color:var(--ink-soft); font-size:15.5px; line-height:1.75; }
  .legal-prose p { margin-top:0.85rem; }
  .legal-prose ul { margin-top:0.85rem; padding-left:1.25rem; list-style:disc; }
  .legal-prose li { margin-top:0.35rem; }
  .legal-prose strong { color:var(--ink); font-weight:600; }
  .legal-prose a { color:var(--blue-deep); font-weight:600; border-bottom:1.5px solid currentColor; }
</style>

<section class="bg-[var(--white)]">
  <div class="legal-wrap mx-auto px-6 pt-[120px] pb-8 sm:pt-[144px]">
    <div class="eyebrow mb-4 flex items-center gap-2.5">
      <span class="tick" style="background:var(--blue);"></span>Legal
    </div>
    <h1 class="font-display text-[var(--ink)]"
        style="font-size:clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem); line-height:1.08; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:-0.025em;">
      Privacy Policy
    </h1>
    <p class="text-[14px] text-[var(--ink-soft)] mt-4">Last updated: <%= lastUpdated %></p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="bg-[var(--white)] pb-24">
  <div class="legal-wrap mx-auto px-6 legal-prose">

    <p>
      This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>OrgTP, LLC</strong> ("OrgTP",
      "we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, and shares information when you use
      the OTP platform and website at <strong>orgtp.com</strong> (the
      "Service"). By using the Service, you agree to this Policy.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Information we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Account information</strong> you provide, such as name, email, organization, and authentication identifiers.</li>
      <li><strong>Content and data</strong> you submit, including charts, scorecards, meetings, and operating content.</li>
      <li><strong>Usage data</strong>, such as pages viewed, features used, device and browser information, and IP address.</li>
      <li><strong>Cookies and similar technologies</strong> used to keep you signed in and to understand how the Service is used.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How we use information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To provide, maintain, and improve the Service;</li>
      <li>To authenticate you and secure your account;</li>
      <li>To communicate with you about the Service, including service and billing notices;</li>
      <li>To provide AI-assisted features you request;</li>
      <li>To comply with legal obligations and enforce our Terms.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How we share information</h2>
    <p>We do not sell your personal information. We share information only:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>With <strong>service providers</strong> (such as hosting, authentication, payment, email, and AI providers) who process data on our behalf under appropriate confidentiality and security obligations;</li>
      <li>Within your <strong>organization</strong>, where the Service is collaborative by design and your teammates can see shared content;</li>
      <li>To the <strong>public library</strong>, only for content you choose to publish;</li>
      <li>When required by <strong>law</strong> or to protect rights, safety, and the integrity of the Service;</li>
      <li>In connection with a <strong>business transfer</strong> such as a merger or acquisition.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Subprocessors and AI providers</h2>
    <p>
      The Service relies on third-party infrastructure and AI providers to
      operate. These providers process data solely to deliver their service to
      us and are bound by their own privacy and security commitments.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Data retention</h2>
    <p>
      We retain your information for as long as your account is active or as
      needed to provide the Service, comply with legal obligations, resolve
      disputes, and enforce our agreements. You may request deletion of your
      account data as described below.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Security</h2>
    <p>
      We use reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your
      information. No system is perfectly secure, and we cannot guarantee
      absolute security.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Your rights and choices</h2>
    <p>
      Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct,
      export, or delete your personal information, and to object to or restrict
      certain processing. To exercise these rights, contact us at
      <a href="mailto:privacy@orgtp.com">privacy@orgtp.com</a>. You can also
      manage many settings directly within your account.
    </p>

    <h2>8. International users</h2>
    <p>
      The Service is operated in the United States. If you access it from
      outside the United States, you understand your information may be
      transferred to and processed in the United States.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Children</h2>
    <p>
      The Service is not directed to children under 18, and we do not knowingly
      collect personal information from them.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Changes to this Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Policy from time to time. If we make material changes,
      we will provide reasonable notice. Your continued use of the Service after
      changes take effect constitutes acceptance of the updated Policy.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about your privacy? Contact <strong>OrgTP, LLC</strong> at
      <a href="mailto:privacy@orgtp.com">privacy@orgtp.com</a>.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-10">
      See also our <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>.
    </p>

  </div>
</section>
